      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark cases for rotating-frame Navier-Stokes; no custom discretisation routines.",
      "rationale": "Standard ANSYS Fluent solver benchmarks for rotating machinery (Taylor-Couette and lid-driven cavity) reproduced within published tolerances. No custom code modifications introduced."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for hemolysis index QoI on three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three meshes (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells) used for Richardson extrapolation. GCI for relative hemolysis index at the nominal operating point is 3.2%, within the 5% threshold. Medium mesh (5.8M) adopted for parametric sweep balancing accuracy and computational cost."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "In-vitro test conditions documented including fluid properties, rotational speed, flow rate, and ambient environment; deviations from nominal COU conditions recorded.",
      "rationale": "Laboratory test conditions fully documented: bovine blood surrogate (viscosity 3.2 mPa·s at 22°C), flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM. Temperature held at 22°C ± 0.5°C; pressure at 101.3 kPa ± 0.2 kPa. A single supplementary run at 37°C was performed for the 4 L/min, 2750 RPM nominal point to partially characterise thermal sensitivity; however, the operating-theatre deployment envelope (18–28°C ambient, potential hypobaric transport at up to 2400 m altitude, EMI from surgical imaging systems) was not systematically characterised. No multi-factor environmental sensitivity study was conducted, and the accepted test conditions do not bound the full range of deployment environments."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH within ±15% of measured RH at all five operating points; statistical metric (NRMSE) < 10%.",
      "rationale": "RH predictions at all five operating points fall within ±8% of measured values. NRMSE across the operating-point matrix is 5.4%, satisfying the acceptance criterion. Comparison performed exclusively against laboratory data collected at 22°C and atmospheric pressure."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly corresponds to the regulatory acceptance criterion and clinical endpoint of pump-induced haemolysis.",
      "rationale": "RH is the primary regulatory metric for CPB device haemolysis per FDA guidance and ASTM F1841. The CFD QoI maps directly to the clinical endpoint. Relevance is unaffected by the environmental characterisation gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry matches the FDA generic centrifugal pump; operating points span the clinical flow-speed envelope; blood analogue properties representative of clinical use.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry with impeller and volute dimensions matching the COU device within manufacturing tolerances. Five operating points span the clinical range (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Blood analogue viscosity at 22°C approximates in-vivo viscosity at 37°C within 12%. Relevance to the geometric and hydraulic aspects of the COU is established. Environmental relevance (temperature range, pressure, EMI) is not addressed by the validation activities."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residuals converge to < 1×10⁻⁵ for all transport equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residuals below 1×10⁻⁵ for continuity, momentum, and turbulence equations. Mass imbalance across the pump domain is 0.004%. No solver divergence events recorded across the parametric sweep."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions and material properties traceable to documented sources.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup conducted by a second CFD analyst not involved in case preparation. Boundary conditions and fluid properties traceable to documented laboratory measurements and published blood rheology data. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law correlation justified by literature and sensitivity study; model-form uncertainty estimated.",
      "rationale": "k-ω SST turbulence model selected based on published rotating-machinery validation studies. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation applied; sensitivity to exponent uncertainty (±10%) evaluated showing < 6% change in RH. Model-form uncertainty estimated at ±9% and incorporated into the output comparison. Fluid properties assumed constant at laboratory conditions; temperature-dependent viscosity effects on hemolysis correlation not modelled."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity of RH to inlet boundary condition uncertainty and fluid property uncertainty quantified; dominant inputs identified.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for inlet flow rate (±5%), rotational speed (±1%), and fluid viscosity (±10%). Viscosity is the dominant input, contributing 61% of output variance. Viscosity value fixed at 22°C laboratory measurement; temperature-dependent variation across the deployment range (18–28°C) was not propagated through the sensitivity analysis. Achieved level meets the MRL 2 requirement for input characterisation at laboratory conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least three independent test replicates per operating point; sample preparation documented.",
      "rationale": "Three independent test replicates performed at each of the five operating points using freshly prepared bovine blood surrogate batches. Haematocrit and viscosity measured for each batch. Coefficient of variation across replicates < 7% for all operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
